      <abstract>
        <p>Felt, new restaurant in West Hollywood, features felt everywhere; photo (Currents) (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Felt is identified with German artists (Joseph Beuys), German hausfraus (for slippers and housecoats) and arts and crafts classes all over the world. The utilitarian pressed fabric, which comes in many colors, is now white hot. A new restaurant in West Hollywood called Felt, above, features felt everywhere.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Felt is identified with German artists (Joseph Beuys), German hausfraus (for slippers and housecoats) and arts and crafts classes all over the world. The utilitarian pressed fabric, which comes in many colors, is now white hot. A new restaurant in West Hollywood called Felt, above, features felt everywhere.</p>
        <p>The architects Ralph Gentile and Sophie Harvey created a place with chocolate brown felt-covered columns and a bar, stools and a stack of large donuts clad in Brady Bunch rusty orange felt that could pass as a set for ''That 70's Show.'' Felt is at 8279 Santa Monica Boulevard; (323) 822-3888.</p>
